```

### From Source

```bash
git clone https://github.com/veriflow/verilog-flow.git
cd verilog-flow
pip install -e ".[dev]"
```

## Quick Start

### 1. Define a Timing Scenario (Stage 2)

Create a YAML file describing your test scenario:

```yaml
# fifo_write_scenario.yaml
scenario: "FIFO_Write_Burst"
description: "Test FIFO write operations with burst transfers"

parameters:
  DEPTH: 4
  DATA_WIDTH: 32

clocks:
  clk:
    period: "5ns"  # 200MHz

phases:
  - name: "Reset_Phase"
    duration_ns: 50
    signals:
      rst_n: 0
      wr_en: 0
      rd_en: 0
    assertions:
      - "full == 0"
      - "empty == 1"

  - name: "Write_Phase"
    duration_ns: 20
    repeat:
      count: "$DEPTH"
      var: "i"
    signals:
      rst_n: 1
      wr_en: 1
      wr_data: "$i * 2"
    assertions:
      - "full == 0 until i == $DEPTH-1"
```

### 2. Validate and Process (Python API)

```python
from verilog_flow.stage2 import parse_yaml_scenario, validate_scenario
from verilog_flow.stage2 import generate_wavedrom, generate_golden_trace

# Load and parse YAML
with open("fifo_write_scenario.yaml") as f:
    yaml_content = f.read()

scenario = parse_yaml_scenario(yaml_content)

# Validate against schema
result = validate_scenario(scenario.to_dict())
if not result.valid:
    print("Validation errors:", result.errors)
else:
    print("✓ Scenario validated successfully")

# Generate WaveDrom waveform
html = generate_wavedrom(scenario, output_path="waveform.html")
print("✓ Waveform saved to waveform.html")

# Generate Golden Trace
trace = generate_golden_trace(scenario)
trace.save("golden_trace.json")
print("✓ Golden trace saved to golden_trace.json")
```

### 3. Command Line Usage

```bash
# Validate a scenario
verilog-flow validate scenario.yaml

# Generate waveform
verilog-flow waveform scenario.yaml --output wave.html

# Generate golden trace
verilog-flow trace scenario.yaml --output trace.json

# Full Stage 2 processing
verilog-flow stage2 scenario.yaml --waveform --trace --validate
```

## Project Structure

```
verilog-flow/
├── verilog_flow/                 # Main package
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── common/                   # Shared utilities
│   │   ├── kpi.py               # KPI tracking
│   │   ├── experience_db.py     # Experience database
│   │   └── logger.py            # Logging utilities
│   ├── stage1/                  # Micro-architecture spec
│   │   ├── spec_generator.py
│   │   └── architect.py
│   ├── stage2/                  # Virtual timing modeling
│   │   ├── yaml_dsl.py          # YAML DSL parser
│   │   ├── validator.py         # Schema validation
│   │   ├── golden_trace.py      # Trace generation
│   │   └── wavedrom_gen.py      # Waveform generation
│   ├── stage3/                  # Code generation
│   ├── stage4/                  # Simulation
│   ├── stage5/                  # Synthesis
│   └── cli/                     # Command-line interface
├── examples/                     # Example scenarios
├── schemas/                      # JSON schemas
├── templates/                    # Code templates
├── tests/                        # Test suite
├── docs/                         # Documentation
├── pyproject.toml               # Project configuration
└── README.md                    # This file
```

